header.gameNote: CBE CLASSIC AT PALO ALTO CA

article.description: Long Beach State 86, San Jose State 67
article.headline: Long Beach State 86, San Jose State 67
article.linkText: Long Beach State 86, San Jose State 67
article.story: STANFORD, Calif. (AP) -- Sterling Byrd had 20 points and six rebounds and Long Beach State beat San Jose State 86-67 in a consolation game of the CBE Classic on Wednesday night. Kejuan Johnson added 13 points, six rebounds, three steals and three assists for the 49ers (1-1), the preseason pick to win the Big West Conference. They used a 12-3 run to start the second half and pull away at Stanford's Maples Pavilion a night after losing 69-68 in a first-round matchup with Air Force. Long Beach State shot 60.6 percent in the second half, going 3-for-8 from 3-point range while holding the cold-shooting Spartans to 33 percent. Tim Pierce, a transfer from Arizona State, scored 19 points and grabbed six rebounds to lead the Spartans, but also committed five of the team's 22 turnovers. Kerry Wooldridge added 12 points and 10 rebounds for San Jose State, which was outrebounded (43-41) for the first time in its three games this season. Jamon Hill finished with 12 points and three assists and is San Jose State's only player to score in double digits in every game so far. But the sloppy Spartans (0-3) struggled to get good shots and committed nine turnovers early, though they were able to keep the game close thanks to the 49ers' inconsistent shooting. Byrd scored his team's first seven points and finished 8-for-12 with three 3-pointers for the 49ers, who took advantage of foul trouble all game by San Jose State center Menelik Barbary. He played only six minutes in the first half, then picked up his third foul 37 seconds into the second half and was held to two points in seven minutes. The Spartans, who made 21-of-26 free throws, won last season's meeting 69-56 in Long Beach and the schools are set to play again in non-conference action Dec. 17 in San Jose.
